§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $X, Y: Ω → 𝗥$ be random variables on probability space
    $(Ω, ℱ, 𝗣)$. ⦉

  ‖ The ❬joint cumulative distribution function❭ denoted
    $\rvcdf{X,Y}: 𝗥^2 → [0, 1]$ is defined by $\rvcdf{X,Y}(s,t) =
    𝗣[X ≤ s, Y ≤ t]$. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ In general the ❬joint cdf❭ for a random vector $X: Ω →
    𝗥^n$ is $\rvcdf{X}: 𝗥^d → [0,1]$ defined by $\rvcdf{X}(t) =
    𝗣[X ≤ t]$ where $x ≤ t$ means $x_i ≤ t_i$ for all $i$. ⦉
⦉

